# ==========================================================
# PROJECT: CACTUS Logistics OS
# FILENAME: .gitignore
# PURPOSE: Tells Git which files to NEVER upload to GitHub.
#
# WHAT THIS FILE DOES:
# Every line below is a file or folder pattern that Git will
# completely ignore. This protects your secrets, keeps your
# repository clean, and prevents sensitive credentials from
# ever being exposed publicly.
# ==========================================================


# ----------------------------------------------------------
# SECRETS & ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES
# The most important section. These files contain your
# Supabase keys, API keys, and passwords. If these ever
# reached GitHub, your accounts could be compromised.
# ----------------------------------------------------------
.env
.env.local
.env.development
.env.production
.env.staging
*.pem


# ----------------------------------------------------------
# NODE.JS (Your backend runtime environment)
# "node_modules" is a folder that gets auto-created when you
# run "npm install". It can contain 100,000+ files and is
# enormous. It never belongs in GitHub because anyone can
# recreate it by running "npm install" themselves.
# ----------------------------------------------------------
node_modules/
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*


# ----------------------------------------------------------
# NEXT.JS (Your frontend framework)
# These are auto-generated build folders that Next.js creates
# when compiling your code. Never commit these.
# ----------------------------------------------------------
.next/
out/
build/


# ----------------------------------------------------------
# OPERATING SYSTEM FILES
# Mac and Windows create hidden files automatically for their
# own internal use. These have no place in your codebase.
# ----------------------------------------------------------

# macOS
.DS_Store
.AppleDouble
.LSOverride
Thumbs.db


# ----------------------------------------------------------
# CODE EDITORS & IDEs
# (Integrated Development Environment — your coding app)
# VS Code creates personal settings folders that are specific
# to your machine and should not be shared.
#
# Cursor is handled with surgical precision: everything under
# .cursor/ is ignored EXCEPT .cursor/rules/, which holds the
# project's coding constitution (cactus-standards.mdc). Rules
# are project-essential and must be tracked so future Claude
# sessions across any machine read the same standards.
# ----------------------------------------------------------
.vscode/
.cursor/*
!.cursor/rules/
*.suo
*.ntvs*
*.njsproj
*.sln


# ----------------------------------------------------------
# LOGS & DIAGNOSTICS
# Log files are generated automatically when things run or
# crash. They are temporary and machine-specific.
# ----------------------------------------------------------
logs/
*.log


# ----------------------------------------------------------
# TESTING & COVERAGE REPORTS
# Auto-generated when you run tests. Recreatable anytime.
# ----------------------------------------------------------
coverage/
.nyc_output/


# ----------------------------------------------------------
# PACKAGE MANAGER LOCK CONFLICTS
# Keep package-lock.json (npm) but ignore yarn if you're
# only using npm, to avoid lock file conflicts.
# ----------------------------------------------------------
yarn.lock
.claude/
